            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              The difference between dampproofing and waterproofing isn't just cost - it's the difference 
              between a dry basement and chronic water problems. While OBC minimum requirements allow 
              dampproofing in well-drained soils, Toronto's clay soil and variable water table often 
              justify the upgrade to waterproofing.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              For a typical 200mm foundation wall on a 2-storey house, dampproofing costs $10-20 per square 
              meter while waterproofing runs $35-50. On a 200m² foundation, that's a difference of about 
              $5,000-8,000. Compare that to the cost of interior waterproofing after the fact ($15,000+) 
              or ongoing water damage, and the upgrade often makes sense.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              At Toronto Concrete, we assess each site individually. Good drainage and sandy soil? 
              Dampproofing works fine. Clay soil, high water table, or any doubt? We recommend waterproofing. 
              It's much cheaper to do it right during construction than to fix water problems later.
            </p>
